SIMPLE: therefore
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Therefore
<hw>There"fore</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>conj. & adv.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>therfore</ets>. See <er>There</er>, and <er>Fore</er>,
<pos>adv.</pos>, <er>For</er>, and cf. <er>Therefor</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>For that or this reason, referring to something
previously stated; for that.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have married a wife, and <qex>therefore</qex> I can not
come.</q> <rj><qau>Luke xiv. 20.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Behold, we have forsaken all, and followed thee; what shall we
have <qex>therefore</qex>?</q> <rj><qau>Matt. xix. 27.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Consequently; by consequence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He blushes; <qex>therefore</qex> he is guilty.</q>
<rj><qau>Spectator.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Then</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Therefrom</ent>⟦br⟧
